-- S.Africa's Alexander Forbes says Marsh & McLennan to take stake at listing
-- By Tiisetso Motsoeneng
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 03:37AM EDT
-- None



JOHANNESBURG, June 23 (Reuters) - South Africa's Alexander Forbes confirmed on Monday it intended to float unlisted shares on the Johannesburg bourse and that a unit of Marsh & McLennan <MMC.N> would become a strategic investor with 34 percent stake after the listing.

Some preference Alexander Forbes' shares <AFPJ.J> are already listed on the JSE. "We are proud to announce that following the evaluation of various strategic options for the group, we are progressing with a listing," said Edward Kieswetter, chief executive of the financial services company. He did not give details how many shares would be sold and at what price when the listing happens on July 24.